>The dizzy is 043 905 205K.  The nearest I could find in the archive
>dizzy page was 043 905 205D, for a '71 bus.

Try http://www.oldvolkshome.com/ovhignbo.htm - it lists an 043 905
205J
for a '75 Beetle Auto-stick, fuel-injection.  The original application
for your distributor is probably closer to that.  Is there a Bosch
number
(like 0 231 xxx yyy) on it?

>Would this be a refinement of the same dizzy, or something different
>altogether?

With most parts, as the letters at the end go up, the part gets
better.
With a distributor, though, it usually means an advance curve change -
not necessarily "better", just "different".

Good luck!

Matt Roberds




